Key Match Events: Josh Inglis scored 103 off 49 balls, helping Australia reach 196-4 off 20 overs.
Marcus Stoinis claimed four wickets, contributing significantly to Australia's win.
George Munsey struck 17 off Xavier Bartlett’s first over, giving Scotland a blistering start.
Brandon McMullen was out to a fine running catch by Tim David, which was a turning point in the match.
Six Australian bowlers took at least one wicket as Scotland were all out for 126.
Post-Match Reflections: Mitchell Marsh praised Josh Inglis and Cameron Green for getting Australia out of trouble and highlighted the team's all-round performance.
Marsh mentioned the possibility of changes in the team for the final match and emphasized the opportunity to win the series 3-0.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Foggy conditions delayed the start of the match by 30 minutes.
Brad Currie was Scotland’s star bowler, taking key wickets including that of Jake Fraser-McGurk and Cameron Green.
